TITLE: Understanding AttributeQueryValue JSON Structure in React Awesome Query Builder
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates the structure of an AttributeQueryValue object in the JsonTree format. It shows the internal ID generation by RAQB, the group and rule types, and how field properties are defined including operators and value types.
SOURCE: https://github.com/calcom/cal.com/blob/main/packages/app-store/routing-forms/README.md#2025-04-20_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: json
CODE:
```
{
    id: "Some-id-generated-and-used-internally-by-raqb"
    type: "group",
    children1: {
        "Some-other-id-generated-and-used-internally-by-raqb": {
            type: "rule",
            properties: {
                field: "ATTRIBUTE.id",
                operator: "multiselect_equals", // One of many operators possible
                value: ["AttributeOption.id"],
                // This is the type of the attribute and the operator corresponds to it. The data provided to jsonLogic on which the logic(generated from RAQB config and this queryValue) is applied must also be as per the requirement of the operator.
                valueType: ["multiselect"] 
            }
        }
    }

}
```

