TITLE: Defining an Image Collection in YAML Front Matter
DESCRIPTION: This YAML front matter block defines an 'items' list containing three JPEG image filenames. This configuration pattern is commonly used to associate multiple images with a document or page in static site generators like Jekyll, Hugo, or Next.js.
SOURCE: https://github.com/calcom/cal.com/blob/main/packages/app-store/mock-payment-app/DESCRIPTION.md#2025-04-20_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: yaml
CODE:
```
---
items:
  - 1.jpeg
  - 2.jpeg
  - 3.jpeg
---
```

----------------------------------------

